This form is close to the standard form Bussière D II 1. The shape of its nozzle is different: it is a hybrid nozzle form mixing Bus. 3 and Bus. 4g. Shoulder: Loeschcke form VII b. Discus decors: for cat. 301 an amphora (similar to cat. 339, for cat. 304 a lion. Base marked off by one circular groove. Cat. 304 has a plain *planta pedis.* Date: Late Flavian to Hadrianic.
